The evidence with the title 'Border arrests fall, deportations soar in Trump's first year - The ... ' says 5 days ago  ... Border Patrol arrests plunged to a 45 - year low , but detentions by deportation officers away from the U.S.-Mexico border soared during president Donald Trump's first months in office,  ... ICE said “ interior removals ” — people deported after being arrested away from the border — jumped 25 percent to 81,603 . 
